&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROYAL NATIONAL ORTHOPAEDIC HOSPITAL NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TRUST DOCTOR IN FOOT AND ANKLE SURGERY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal National Orthopaedic Hospital provides a comprehensive range of neuro-musculoskeletal health care which is unique within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the above position, which will commence in April 2021 for 6 months. This position is within the Foot &amp; Ankle Department and is supported by 3 Specialist Registrars and 4 Consultants&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointee would be expected to work closely with the 4 Foot &amp; Ankle surgeons and the multi-disciplinary team in the management of patients.The post is based predominantly at the Stanmore site, although the successful candidate will be expected to undertake outpatient clinics in central London at our Bolsover Street outpatient department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Demonstration of a commitment to training in orthopaedic surgery, good communication and team working skills are essential. Other experience in the form of audit or research is desirable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 25/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frances Carney&lt;/strong&gt; in the Foot &amp; Ankle Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;on &lt;strong&gt;020 8385 3017&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
